{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886892874,"sessionID":"ses_284e4c77bffeyVf72lfyaoO6ju","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1b7b840012OPs7U7xspJqzd","messageID":"msg_d7b1b68dc001oBsvQKifMVObHA","sessionID":"ses_284e4c77bffeyVf72lfyaoO6ju","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-21b6e1f01e99403fbb141d3979e80223","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) |\n8: | Module | `docker` |\n9: | Language | Dockerfile |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: WorkloadManager Dockerfile Foundation (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create builder stage with golang:1.24-alpine base\n20:   - Purpose: Define builder stage for Go compilation\n21:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n22:   - Verification: `grep \"FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\" docker/Dockerfile`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Add go.mod/go.sum COPY and cache mount for module download\n25:   - Purpose: Optimize module download with BuildKit cache\n26:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n27:   - Verification: `grep \"RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod\" docker/Dockerfile`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Add source COPY and CGO_ENABLED=0 environment\n30:   - Purpose: Prepare source for static compilation\n31:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n32:   - Verification: `grep \"CGO_ENABLED=0\" docker/Dockerfile`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Add go build with ldflags optimization and build cache mount\n35:   - Purpose: Build optimized binary with stripped symbols\n36:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n37:   - Verification: `grep \"ldflags=\\\"-w -s\\\"\" docker/Dockerfile && grep \"go build\" docker/Dockerfile`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.5**: Create runtime stage with alpine:3.19 base\n40:   - Purpose: Define minimal runtime base image\n41:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n42:   - Verification: `grep \"FROM alpine:3.19\" docker/Dockerfile`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T1.6**: Add ca-certificates and tzdata packages\n45:   - Purpose: Install TLS certs and timezone data\n46:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n47:   - Verification: `grep \"apk add --no-cache ca-certificates tzdata\" docker/Dockerfile`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T1.7**: Create non-root user apiserver (UID 1000)\n50:   - Purpose: Add security through non-root execution\n51:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n52:   - Verification: `grep \"adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\" docker/Dockerfile`\n53: \n54: - [ ] **T1.8**: COPY binary from builder stage to runtime\n55:   - Purpose: Extract compiled binary from builder\n56:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n57:   - Verification: `grep \"COPY --from=builder\" docker/Dockerfile && grep \"workloadmanager\" docker/Dockerfile`\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T1.9**: Set USER 1000 and EXPOSE 8080\n60:   - Purpose: Configure security context and port\n61:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n62:   - Verification: `grep \"USER 1000\" docker/Dockerfile && grep \"EXPOSE 8080\" docker/Dockerfile`\n63: \n64: - [ ] **T1.10**: Set ENTRYPOINT for workloadmanager binary\n65:   - Purpose: Define container entrypoint\n66:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n67:   - Verification: `grep \"ENTRYPOINT \\[\\\"/app/bin/workloadmanager\\\"\\]\" docker/Dockerfile`\n68: \n69: ### Phase 2: Router Dockerfile Foundation (ST-2)\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create builder stage with golang:1.24-alpine base\n72:   - Purpose: Define builder stage for Go compilation\n73:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n74:   - Verification: `grep \"FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\" docker/Dockerfile.router`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.2**: Add go.mod/go.sum COPY and cache mount for module download\n77:   - Purpose: Optimize module download with BuildKit cache\n78:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n79:   - Verification: `grep \"RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod\" docker/Dockerfile.router`\n80: \n81: - [ ] **T2.3**: Add source COPY including client-go/\n82:   - Purpose: Include client-go module for router\n83:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n84:   - Verification: `grep \"COPY client-go/ client-go/\" docker/Dockerfile.router`\n85: \n86: - [ ] **T2.4**: Add CGO_ENABLED=0 and go build with ldflags\n87:   - Purpose: Build optimized router binary\n88:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n89:   - Verification: `grep \"CGO_ENABLED=0\" docker/Dockerfile.router && grep \"./cmd/router\" docker/Dockerfile.router`\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T2.5**: Create runtime stage with alpine:3.19 base\n92:   - Purpose: Define minimal runtime base image\n93:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n94:   - Verification: `grep \"FROM alpine:3.19\" docker/Dockerfile.router`\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T2.6**: Add ca-certificates, tzdata, and non-root user router (UID 1000)\n97:   - Purpose: Install packages and create security user\n98:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n99:   - Verification: `grep \"adduser -D -u 1000 router\" docker/Dockerfile.router`\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T2.7**: COPY router binary from builder and set USER 1000\n102:   - Purpose: Extract binary and configure security\n103:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n104:   - Verification: `grep \"/app/bin/router\" docker/Dockerfile.router && grep \"USER 1000\" docker/Dockerfile.router`\n105: \n106: - [ ] **T2.8**: Set EXPOSE 8080 and ENTRYPOINT for router binary\n107:   - Purpose: Configure port and entrypoint\n108:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n109:   - Verification: `grep \"ENTRYPOINT \\[\\\"/app/bin/router\\\"\\]\" docker/Dockerfile.router`\n110: \n111: ### Phase 3: PicoD Dockerfile Foundation (ST-3)\n112: \n113: - [ ] **T3.1**: Create builder stage with golang:1.24 base (not Alpine)\n114:   - Purpose: Use standard golang image for Ubuntu runtime compatibility\n115:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n116:   - Verification: `grep \"FROM golang:1.24 AS builder\" docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T3.2**: Add go.mod/go.sum COPY and go mod download (no cache mount)\n119:   - Purpose: Download modules without BuildKit cache for simplicity\n120:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n121:   - Verification: `grep \"go mod download\" docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n122: \n123: - [ ] **T3.3**: Add source COPY, CGO_ENABLED=0, and go build for picod\n124:   - Purpose: Build picod binary for sandbox management\n125:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n126:   - Verification: `grep \"./cmd/picod\" docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n127: \n128: - [ ] **T3.4**: Create runtime stage with ubuntu:24.04 base\n129:   - Purpose: Ubuntu base for Python3 sandbox support\n130:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n131:   - Verification: `grep \"FROM ubuntu:24.04\" docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n132: \n133: - [ ] **T3.5**: Install python3, python3-pip, ca-certificates packages\n134:   - Purpose: Install code execution dependencies\n135:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n136:   - Verification: `grep \"python3\" docker/Dockerfile.picod && grep \"apt-get install\" docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n137: \n138: - [ ] **T3.6**: COPY picod binary from builder (no USER directive - runs as root)\n139:   - Purpose: Extract binary with root privileges for sandbox management\n140:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n141:   - Verification: `grep \"COPY --from=builder\" docker/Dockerfile.picod && grep \"/app/bin/picod\" docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n142: \n143: - [ ] **T3.7**: Set EXPOSE 8080 and ENTRYPOINT for picod binary\n144:   - Purpose: Configure port and entrypoint\n145:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n146:   - Verification: `grep \"ENTRYPOINT \\[\\\"/app/bin/picod\\\"\\]\" docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n147: \n148: ### Phase 4: Makefile Build Targets (ST-4)\n149: \n150: - [ ] **T4.1**: Add docker-build target for WorkloadManager\n151:   - Purpose: Add Makefile target for building workloadmanager image\n152:   - File: `Makefile`\n153:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-build:\" Makefile && grep \"docker/Dockerfile\" Makefile`\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T4.2**: Add docker-build-router target\n156:   - Purpose: Add Makefile target for building router image\n157:   - File: `Makefile`\n158:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-build-router:\" Makefile && grep \"Dockerfile.router\" Makefile`\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T4.3**: Add docker-build-picod target\n161:   - Purpose: Add Makefile target for building picod image\n162:   - File: `Makefile`\n163:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-build-picod:\" Makefile && grep \"Dockerfile.picod\" Makefile`\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T4.4**: Add docker-build-all aggregate target\n166:   - Purpose: Build all three images with single target\n167:   - File: `Makefile`\n168:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-build-all:\" Makefile`\n169: \n170: - [ ] **T4.5**: Add docker-buildx-push targets for multi-arch builds\n171:   - Purpose: Support linux/amd64,linux/arm64 multi-arch builds\n172:   - File: `Makefile`\n173:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-buildx-push\" Makefile && grep \"linux/amd64,linux/arm64\" Makefile`\n174: \n175: ### Phase 5: Dockerfile Syntax Validation (ST-5)\n176: \n177: - [ ] **T5.1**: Verify all three Dockerfiles exist\n178:   - Purpose: Confirm Dockerfile files created\n179:   - File: `docker/`\n180:   - Verification: `test -f docker/Dockerfile && test -f docker/Dockerfile.router && test -f docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n181: \n182: - [ ] **T5.2**: Verify workloadmanager has multi-stage structure\n183:   - Purpose: Confirm two-stage build pattern\n184:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n185:   - Verification: `grep -c \"FROM\" docker/Dockerfile | grep \"2\"`\n186: \n187: - [ ] **T5.3**: Verify router has multi-stage structure\n188:   - Purpose: Confirm two-stage build pattern\n189:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n190:   - Verification: `grep -c \"FROM\